posts.name: Peter Johnson
posts.cooked:
The key part of that message is “a CANSparkMax instance has already been created with this device ID: 14.”  The stack trace shows where this is happening (ShooterRotation.java line 16).  This can be due to either using the same CAN ID in two different subsystems or instantiating the same subsystem twice.

On a separate note, have you updated your code to 2025 versions yet?  CANSparkMax was removed in 2025 (replaced with just “SparkMax”).

posts.name: Gavin Matthews
posts.cooked: You are creating the ShooterRotation subsystem twice in RobotContainer, on lines 49 and 52. This is not allowed because they would share the same motor.
